Discussions about craft skills and necessity of it nowadays and in history.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give an overview of historical and modern handycraft techniques and possibilities for helping students to acquire the skills of knitting, crocheting and embroidery.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course the student will -	Knows the history of craft techniques and Estonian craft heritage; -	Knows different materials and tools used for knitting, crocheting and embroidery; -	Knows the terminology and uses different modes of marking the patterns; -	Uses basic techniques of knitting, different patterns and stitch types; -	Uses basic crocheting techniques, crotchets tight surfaces and laces; -	Knows and can uses basic embroidery stitches for creating objects inspired from folk art.
